      "question": "A city planning committee is mapping out a new park on a Cartesian plane where the origin $(0, 0)$ represents the City Hall. Three proposed landmarks are located at $A(2, 3)$, $B(6, 7)$, and $C(10, 3)$. A straight walking path is planned to connect $A$ and $C$. A secondary utility line is planned to pass through $B$ and the midpoint of the path $AC$.",
      "type": "case_study",
      "marks": 4,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "i",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "What is the length of the walking path $AC$?",
          "answer": "(B)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $6$ units",
            "(B) $8$ units",
            "(C) $10$ units",
            "(D) $4\\sqrt{2}$ units"
          ],
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Identify coordinates: $A(2, 3)$ and $C(10, 3)$.",
              "Apply distance formula $d = \\sqrt{(x_2 - x_1)^2 + (y_2 - y_1)^2}$.",
              "$d = \\sqrt{(10 - 2)^2 + (3 - 3)^2} = \\sqrt{8^2 + 0^2} = 8$."
            ],
            "derivation": "d = \\sqrt{(10 - 2)^2 + (3 - 3)^2} = \\sqrt{8^2} = 8"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "ii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Find the coordinates of the midpoint $M$ of the path $AC$.",
          "answer": "$(6, 3)$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Use midpoint formula $M = (\\frac{x_1 + x_2}{2}, \\frac{y_1 + y_2}{2})$.",
              "$x = \\frac{2 + 10}{2} = 6$.",
              "$y = \\frac{3 + 3}{2} = 3$."
            ],
            "derivation": "M = (\\frac{2 + 10}{2}, \\frac{3 + 3}{2}) = (6, 3)"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iii",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "If the utility line connects $B(6, 7)$ and the midpoint $M(6, 3)$, what is the nature of this line?",
          "answer": "(C)",
          "options": [
            "(A) Horizontal line",
            "(B) Line passing through origin",
            "(C) Vertical line",
            "(D) Line with slope 1"
          ],
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "The points are $B(6, 7)$ and $M(6, 3)$.",
              "Since the x-coordinates are the same ($x=6$), the line is vertical."
            ],
            "derivation": "x_1 = 6, x_2 = 6 \\Rightarrow \\text{Vertical line}"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iv",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Find the area of $\\triangle ABC$.",
          "answer": "$16$ square units",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Use area of triangle formula $\\frac{1}{2}|x_1(y_2 - y_3) + x_2(y_3 - y_1) + x_3(y_1 - y_2)|$.",
              "Area $= \\frac{1}{2}|2(7 - 3) + 6(3 - 3) + 10(3 - 7)|$.",
              "Area $= \\frac{1}{2}|2(4) + 0 + 10(-4)| = \\frac{1}{2}|8 - 40| = \\frac{1}{2}|-32| = 16$."
            ],
            "derivation": "Area = \\frac{1}{2} |2(7 - 3) + 6(3 - 3) + 10(3 - 7)| = \\frac{1}{2} |8 + 0 - 40| = 16"
          }
        }
      ],
